{
  "doc_id": "26009",
  "text": "Salm. typhimurium DT104:30 was rapidly excluded when it was introduced into feed that has been fermented for >48 h with Pd. Pentosaceus [CITATION_1] . However, the death rate was very temperature dependent. Salm. typhimurium DT104:30 died four to five times faster in feed maintained at 30 o C (D value 34-45 min) compared with feed maintained at 20 o C (D value 137-250 min). It appears that this effect is due to the lactic acid concentration of the fermented feed rather than the presence of any bacteriocins produced by LAB [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
